# MOC Operations

Every project has a single `MOC.md` acting as the control plane.

## Required sections in MOC.md

- `## TL;DR`
- `## Outcome`
- `## Status`
- `## Quick Links` (documentation, decisions, changelog, backlog, meetings, runbooks)
- `## Open Decisions`
- `## Active Backlog`
- `## Recent Changes`
- `## Risks & Blockers`
- `## Next Actions`

## Linking discipline

- Any new project note must be linked from `MOC.md` or from a child index linked by `MOC.md`.
- Use OFM wikilinks only: `[[Projects/<Project Name>/decisions/<note>]]`.
- Prefer one link per line under Quick Links for scannability.

## Style

- Bullets, not prose.
- Append-only for status, decisions, and changes history.
- Keep TL;DR to 1-3 sentences and regenerate on material status change.

## Agent behavior

- When editing a project note, update MOC.md cross-links and the `updated` frontmatter field.
- If a required section is missing in MOC.md, add it without reordering existing sections.
